args: How do you know my fiancé's name?
Because before he was your betrothed,\nhe was mine.
I was to be married off to Elua so the\ngap between North and South Grastaea\nmight finally be bridged.
However, due to the wishes of his nation's\nroyal family, Elua's family chose to marry\nthe third heir to Alberia instead.
But then my love was betrayed by the\nvery woman he was engaged to—\nbetrayed and sent to execution!
So it's about revenge, is it?
Yes! Revenge for my murdered love!\nAnd if I can save my nation from starving\nin the bargain, so much the better.
I trust you sufficiently understand the\nsituation now. If you have any last words,\nI suggest you make them here.
Might I suggest cursing your own name\nfor being so foolish as to bring me to this\nplace alone with you?
Oh, I am not the fool here.
Remember my plan? We were to stay put\nand await good news from Cat Sìth.
And here her news is, right on time!\nBorne by a white sparrow, no less.
I've secured the weapon, Chelle.\nCat-astrophe averted!
Your Highness, are you all right?
I'm fine. Good work, the both of you.
But...that's the knight you didn't want\nat the party!
Did you truly believe we were fighting?\nI'm a better actor than I thought...
But my spies overheard you! Ah! I mean...
There's no need to hide it.\nDiplomatic events are battlefields\nof espionage.
That's why I removed Leif. To cause you\nto drop your guard.
And to get you reveal your true intentions,\nI created this situation and feigned the\nrole of the pure and foolish princess.
Then this was a trap?!\nALL OF THIS was a trap?!
How long have you known that I was\nintending to kill you?
All of these ＂alliance＂ discussions have\njust been my way to suss out Grams'\nattack dog.
We won't be able to avoid Grams\non our journey north.
So we needed a way to determine who\nelse was looking to cause us trouble.
If we laid out the red carpet, I figured\nany country with hostile intentions would\ncome swooping in.
It always pays to know who your\nenemies are—and to eliminate them.
You have played me for the fool.
Oh, we've both been playing the same\ngame—it's the only one we royals really\nknow how to engage in, after all.
Well then, it seems I have lost.
I don't see much of an option at this point;\nwhat plan I had now lies in tatters.
Neither of us can kill the other without\nstarting a war.
As such, I would request that you keep\nthese events secret, and in exchange, you\nmay ask of me whatever your heart desires.
A wise decision. I too have no desire\nto see this situation escalate.
So then, in exchange for remaining mum\nabout this little incident...
I insist we go ahead and formalize the\nalliance between Alberia and Fadden.
Are we to be your puppets, then? Is that it?
These are my terms: First, Fadden and\nAlberia will bring no harm to the other.
Secondly, Fadden and Alberia will create\nand maintain a mutual trade network.
And finally, Fadden and Alberia will agree\nto jointly develop manacaster technology.
But that is the very alliance we\nnegotiated during my visit here!
Yes, and nothing has changed\nin the meantime.
I don't understand! Why would you form\nan equitable alliance with a country that\nhas betrayed you?!
For the sake of future generations.
If we take advantage of you, they will only\ncome to hate us as you do Grams now.
And as I said before, joint development\nof manacasters benefits us as well.
What's more, we now have one less\nenemy in the north, just as I'd hoped.
I believe Fadden hopes for the same?
Diplomacy is about negotiating the most\nbeneficial outcome for one's country,\nnot being swayed by impulse or emotion.
I can forge friendships with people I\ncannot personally forgive if I do so for\nthe sake of my country.
So you can maintain your relationship\nwith Grams...or form a new one with us.
Which one holds the brighter future for\nFadden? Think hard, and do not be swayed\nby something so petty as revenge.
A royal should be ashamed to bring their\npersonal affairs into the governance of\ntheir country.
I... On behalf of Fadden...I choose...
The treaty is signed and sealed.\nAll's well that ends well!
Though I still think you went too easy on\nthem, considering they tried to kill you.
We accomplished our goal, and so long\nas there is no demerit for us, it pays\nto have others in our debt.
Still, it was a bold stroke to raise her tail\nby talking about your old fiancé and such!\nMeowr hawr hawr!
Though even she knew better than to\nreact to it while others were present.
I'm glad it motivated her to carry out the\nassassination. It allowed me to hear her\ntrue feelings.
You may be happy, but I still personally\nobject to your being placed in such a\nrisky situation, Princess.
A master must use every piece on her\nchessboard—even the queen.
And besides, once my little kittens gave\nyou the word, you stormed in to save me.
I've always dreamed of a handsome\nprince riding to my rescue!
I would ask what would have happened\nif I'd been late, but I know you were more\nthan prepared to defend yourself.
That little number is small enough to stay\nhidden in my dress—and I really MUST\nthank those scientists.
Still, I'm glad I didn't have to use it;\nviolence has no place in diplomacy.
Princess Yelda didn't understand that.\nThough to be fair, I imagine it was the\nCardinal who pushed her into this.
Speaking of, since I'm headed that way\nanyway, I think it's time I had him dance\nwith me as well.
...Pray take care of yourself.\nI await your safe return.
Naturally. You didn't train me up\njust to have me fail now.
And with preparations complete, it's time\nto deploy for a party in the north!
